! Built-in keys

|!Key |!Effect |
|`Ctrl-Space` |Open / reset palette |
|`Tab` |Cycle focus section (within current group) |
|`Shift-Tab` |Jump between pill-group (top strips) and main group (input/menu/details/preview) |
|`↑` `↓` |Move row selection |
|`→` |Drill — descend tree containers, push action menu on typed catalogue rows |
|`←` |Pop one stage |
|`↵` |Fire selected row |
|`Ctrl-↵` |Fire + keep palette open |
|`Alt-↵` |Fire row's primary icon (e.g. 🌐 opens URL in new tab) |
|`Ctrl-Alt-↵` |Fire row icon's secondary action (e.g. 🌐 copies URL) |
|`Space` |Open action menu on any row whose tiddler has applicable actions (works in tree views via `ca-applies` filter); also: toggle / edit kind-specific rows |
|any character |Type-ahead: a printable key pressed in any non-input section that no section gesture claimed jumps focus to the input and appends the character — start typing from anywhere to filter |
|`Esc` |Pop stage; from root, close |
|`Shift-Esc` |Close palette outright |
|`DEL` |Remove focused pill / reset row to default |
|`Ctrl-DEL` |Clear all pills in focused strip |
|`Ctrl-↑` `Ctrl-↓` |Reorder row (when row declares move actions) |
|hold `Ctrl` |Show row detail drawer |

! Leaders (registered live)

The cascade keeps the input focused while you type a leader key — once you stop typing (idle window, default 500ms), the leader fires. Plugins can register new leaders; the table below reflects what's currently in the wiki.

